CM_ SG_ 140 ACCEL_PEDAL "Lower 10 bits of bytes 6-7, scale 0.1%. The upper 6 bits cycle independently and caused 0xFC00 jumps when this was incorrectly decoded as a 16-bit pedal field. Corrected using the timestamped 2026-07-11 drive and cross-checked against 0x3FA.ACCEL_PEDAL_LOW_RATE.";
CM_ BO_ 136 "Redundant longitudinal acceleration estimate. In sampled logs this tracks 0x112.LONG_ACCEL but has a different bias/scale origin; 0x112 remains the preferred longitudinal acceleration source.";
CM_ BO_ 274 "Multi-subframe (64B, 4 subframes) steering sensor on body bus. Carries BRAKE_PRESSED (byte 7 bit 1), TURN_SIGNAL_LEFT, longitudinal accel, redundant 12-bit steering angle. Right turn signal is on 0x58B (R5 splits L/R across buses).";
CM_ BO_ 308 "Byte 16 = CRC-8 (poly 0x1D, XOR 0xEB, body = bytes[17:24]); tail-positioned rather than at byte 4 like every other message in this DBC. Byte 17 high nibble is COUNTER; low nibble is LKA_ACTIVE. Observed raw states are 0, 3, 4, 6, 7, and 8.";
CM_ SG_ 308 STEERING_TORQUE_134 "Byte 10. Originally labeled TORQUE_CMD assuming this was the LKA command, but corpus mining shows it is not correlated with 0x1AB.LKAS_TORQUE_CMD and is usually zero. Exact steering-telemetry semantics are not fully decoded; do not use as a command signal.";
CM_ BO_ 548 "Body-bus pedal/gear status. GEAR_SELECTED, DIRECTION_HI, and DIRECTION_LO are redundant indicators around gear selection; primary openpilot gear state remains 0x12F.";
CM_ BO_ 788 "Camera lane-model/status message. LANE_DETECTED is 0xFF when no lane model is present; non-0xFF values appear during lane-detection/assist contexts.";
CM_ BO_ 847 "Candidate ACC object-status message on bus 0. The two bytes are often 0xFF, but a timestamped 2026-07-11 visual lead/no-lead test did not validate them as direct presence flags: non-0xFF rates were not consistently higher while the cluster showed a lead and were sometimes high before/after it. Do not use these fields as lead-present booleans without decoding the surrounding object payload/state.";
CM_ BO_ 998 "Candidate setpoint telemetry. Byte 6 remained 48 while the displayed setpoint was manually changed through 60-123 km/h on 2026-07-11, so it is not the current driver-selected set speed.";
CM_ BO_ 1100 "Redundant gear-direction enum: 1=reverse, 2=stationary/P/N, 3=forward D/B. Validated against 0x12F gear states in captured gear-cycle and driving logs.";
CM_ BO_ 1107 "Reverse/gear indicator observed in captured gear-cycle logs. REVERSE_LIGHT is high during reverse and some adjacent neutral transition frames.";
CM_ BO_ 1203 "Detected speed-limit bucket. Byte 0 followed DETECTED_SPEED_LIMIT minus 5 in the timestamped 2026-07-11 transitions: 130->125, 100->95, 80->75, and 60->55. Special value 250 pairs with detected limit 255/unset.";
CM_ BO_ 1204 "EPS state byte with a heartbeat bit; low 7 bits carry the state value. Note: bit 31 (EPS_STATE_HEARTBEAT) toggles continuously even with no ADAS activity; do not mistake for an event signal.";
CM_ BO_ 1205 "ADAS_ENGAGED is a multi-state enum. Observed values include 0 and many non-zero states across powered-on, driving, assist, and pre-init contexts; exact per-state semantics are not fully decoded yet.";
CM_ BO_ 1233 "Candidate cruise/ADAS controls. The currently defined distance and button fields remained zero during a timestamped 4->3->2->1->4 distance cycle on 2026-07-11, so their positions are not validated and must not be used by CarState.";
CM_ BO_ 1303 "Detected road-speed-limit message. Byte 2 followed signed limits independently of the driver-selected setpoint, including 130->100->80->60->130 on 2026-07-11 while manual set speeds differed. 0xFF is unset/no detection. This is not the speed currently enforced and not driver intent; the true manual setpoint was not observed on the two intercepted CAN pairs.";
CM_ BO_ 1402 "ADAS state and mode. Byte 5 is the activity state enum. State 0 identifies Active Assist controlling and state 8 armed/standby. State 16 is not merely driver override: it persisted throughout active ACC-only and Speed Limiter operation in the timestamped 2026-07-11 mode cycle, and also appears during Active Assist steering override. Byte 6 must be decoded as a full mode-state byte: observed 0x02 with Active Assist controlling, 0x91 during its driver override, 0x41 when selected/available, 0x90 during longitudinal-only/override contexts, and 0x40 while off/armed. The former one-bit ACTIVE_ASSIST_SELECTED definition was invalid and was removed.";
CM_ BO_ 1416 "Controlled front-door and belt transitions on 2026-07-11 did not validate the current DOOR_DRIVER_OPEN_CANDIDATE or BELT_UNBUCKLED_CANDIDATE: they did not stay asserted for the commanded states and sometimes toggled together. Do not expose them through CarState until individually isolated.";
CM_ SG_ 1018 VEHICLE_SPEED_MPH "Byte 4 carries vehicle speed in MPH (not km/h as labeled in early reverse-engineering); scale 1.609 converts to km/h. WHEEL_SPEEDS_226 is the preferred speed source.";
CM_ SG_ 1018 SPEED_LIKE_HIGH_RES "13-bit speed-like field. It tracks speed over parts of the range but wraps/diverges in broader drive mining, so do not use it as the primary vehicle speed.";
CM_ SG_ 1018 UNKNOWN_CONSTANT_115 "Byte 14 remained 115 in Comfort mode across multiple drives, including while actual speed exceeded 115 and the displayed setpoint reached 123 km/h on 2026-07-11. It is therefore not a speed cap or cruise setpoint; exact meaning remains unknown.";
CM_ SG_ 1303 DETECTED_SPEED_LIMIT "Camera-detected road speed limit in km/h. Confirmed across 130/100/90/80/70/60/50/40/30 zones and independent of driver-selected ACC/limiter speed. 0xFF is unset/no detection.";
CM_ SG_ 1303 LONGITUDINAL_ENFORCING_CANDIDATE "Byte 5 bit. Candidate longitudinal-enforcement/status bit observed in ACC/limiter-related contexts, but broader corpus mining also shows it during some armed/override states. Treat as tentative until mode-specific captures fully isolate it.";
CM_ BO_ 1519 "Unknown duplicated telemetry, previously assumed to be the driver-selected setpoint. Both bytes remained 16 while the displayed ACC/Active Assist setpoint was manually moved through 60, 62, 100, 109, 110, and 123 km/h in the timestamped 2026-07-11 drive; do not use as cruiseState.speed.";
CM_ BO_ 1638 "Low-rate body status. BRAKE_PRESSED_LOW_RATE is a redundant brake-pressed indicator and lags/disagrees during transitions, so 0x112 remains preferred.";
CM_ BO_ 1661 "Motor RPM broadcast observed on both captured buses.";

VAL_ 303 GEAR_STATE 1 "R" 2 "N" 3 "B" 8 "D" ;
